\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 \line Appreciation of the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://religiousnaturalism.org/natural-wonders/"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 wonders}}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~of our lives and our world\line A sense of humility and gratitude\line A sense of responsibility (to try to act in ways that will contribute to what is seen as good)}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\line }{\f0\fs24\b0 H}{\f0\fs24\b0 aught emphasizes that theology looks for levels of meaning and truth that scientific method is not wired to receive. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Theology has its own horizon of inquiry. It is grounded in a qualitatively distinct set of questions from those asked by scientists and ethicists. The data that give rise to distinctively theological questions include an easily recognizable set of beliefs and ethical commitments that do not show up within the horizon of scientific inquiry, but which every scientist must embrace in order to do science at all.}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0 1.	}{\f0\fs24\b0 B}{\f0\fs24\b0 elief (faith or trust) that the world, including the horizon of scientific inquiry, is intelligible.}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0 2.	}{\f0\fs24\b0 B}{\f0\fs24\b0 elief that truth is worth seeking.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0 3.	}{\f0\fs24\b0 B}{\f0\fs24\b0 elief that honesty, humility, generosity, and openness in sharing one\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s ideas and discoveries are unconditionally right (and hence that the pursuit of virtue is not irrelevant to successful scientific work.)}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0 4.	}{\f0\fs24\b0 B}{\f0\fs24\b0 elief that one\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s own mind has the capacity to grasp intelligibility and to distinguish what is true from what is false.\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\super [}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i1\super citation needed}}{\f0\fs24\b0\super ]}
